Class GMFFExportFile

java.lang.Object
mmj.gmff.GMFFExportFile
public class GMFFExportFile extends Object
GMFFExportFile is a little helper class for GMFF to handle the ugly IO details.

  • Constructor Details

    • GMFFExportFile

      public GMFFExportFile(GMFFFolder exportFolder, String exportFileName, String charsetEncoding, String exportType, boolean append) throws GMFFException
      Standard constructor.
      Parameters:
      exportFolder - where output files written
      exportFileName - Output File Name.
      charsetEncoding - Charset Encoding Name (see doc).
      exportType - Export Type (e.g. "html" or "althtml")
      append - true only if open in append mode
      Throws:
      GMFFException - if Export File is null or empty, or not a writeable file, or if there is a file security error, or if charsetEncoding name is null or empty.
